. INTERVIEW QUESTIONS & ANSWERS (Most Asked)
Q1: What is the difference between tar and zip?

Answer:

tar only archives; gzip adds compression

zip archives and compresses simultaneously

zip can compress individual files; tar compresses whole archive

Q2: What is rsync and why is it better than scp?

Answer:
rsync transfers only changed blocks, supports resume, and can sync directories.

Q3: What is the use of --delete option in rsync?

Answer:
It deletes files on the destination that are not in source.
Used in mirroring.

Q4: How to check a tar file without extracting?
tar -tvf file.tar.gz

Q5: How do you copy files between two remote servers?
scp user1@serverA:/data/file user2@serverB:/backup


Or:

rsync -avz user1@A:/data user2@B:/backup

Q6: How do you compress multiple folders?
tar -czvf project.tar.gz folder1 folder2 folder3

Q7: How to resume a broken file transfer?
rsync -avzP file.iso user@server:/backup
